      • moveTo

        public void moveTo​(int x,
                   int y)
        Description copied from interface: EditorCell
        Move cell to the specified location. In contrast with EditorCell.setX(int)/EditorCell.setY(int) methods, this method will re-position complete cell structure: this cell together with all child cells. For EditorCell_Collection this method can trigger re-layout process for some child cells by calling EditorCell.requestRelayout() method on corresponding cells.

        For example, if wrapping (indent) layout is attached to this EditorCell_Collection, then layout logic uses X coordinate of first (or parent) cell to determine cell wrapping position. As a result of EditorCell.moveTo(int, int) request, complete re-layout for cell subtree should be triggered to determine new wrapping position.

        In case of EditorCell_Collection this method will delegate all layout-specific cell processing to the corresponding CellLayout

        Specified by:
        moveTo in interface EditorCell
        Overrides:
        moveTo in class EditorCell_Basic
        Parameters:
        x - new X-coordinate
        y - new Y-coordinate
